      "teardown": ["rm -f /tmp/cmcp-replay-crag-empty.db"],
      "prerequisites": [
        {"kind": "file", "path": "tools/crag-mcp/crag-mcp"}
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "crag-mcp/dogfood/session-2026-05-30",
      "_note": [
        "End-to-end butlerbot-shaped session captured under cmcp-tee.",
        "Driven by tools/dogfood-crag-host/ after the v0.6.0 O1 rewrite",
        "+ the v0.7 step-5-via-A4 restore + the step-8 A5 demo, so the",
        "wire shape is what the A1/A2/A4/A5 client helpers produce.",
        "14 RPC calls: initialize, notif/initialized, tools/list,",
        "resources/read, 3x sync tools/call (A2), 3x async tools/call",
        "(A4: dispatched in a burst via tool_call_async, reaped in",
        "reverse order via tool_wait), 2x schema-rejection tools/call",
        "(empty query, k=999 -> result-channel isError per MCP",
        "2025-11-25), 1x tools/call against an unknown tool (-32602),",
        "1x A5 tools/call via cmcp_client_tool_call_text. The A4 burst",
        "is the reason CMCP_WORKERS must be pinned to 1 below: with 3",
        "dispatched requests in flight, a parallel worker pool would",
        "reorder the response frames non-deterministically.",
        "CMCP_WORKERS=1 keeps them in id order so the positional",
        "out-frame comparison holds. DB is an empty file at replay",
        "time so the embed-then-cosine-search path runs but every",
        "result is '(no matching chunks)' - which is stable, hence",
        "reproducible. Embed backend pinned to ollama + mxbai-embed-",
        "large; the fixture skips if the ollama binary is not on PATH."
      ],
      "fixture": "conformance/fixtures/crag-mcp/dogfood/session-2026-05-30.jsonl",
      "server": "tools/crag-mcp/crag-mcp",
      "args": ["--db", "/tmp/cmcp-replay-dogfood.db"],
      "env": {
        "CRAG_EMBED_BACKEND": "ollama",
        "CRAG_EMBED_MODEL": "mxbai-embed-large",
        "CMCP_WORKERS": "1"
      },
      "setup": [
        "rm -f /tmp/cmcp-replay-dogfood.db",
        "touch /tmp/cmcp-replay-dogfood.db"
      ],
      "teardown": ["rm -f /tmp/cmcp-replay-dogfood.db"],
      "output_masks": [
        {"kind": "regex", "path": "/result/contents/0/text",
         "pattern": "db:\\s+\\S+", "replacement": "db:     <masked>"}
      ],
      "prerequisites": [
        {"kind": "file", "path": "tools/crag-mcp/crag-mcp"},
        {"kind": "cmd",  "name": "ollama"}
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "crag-mcp/stats_resource_read",
      "fixture": "conformance/fixtures/crag-mcp/stats_resource_read.jsonl",
      "server": "tools/crag-mcp/crag-mcp",
      "args": ["--db", "$CRAG_TEST_DB"],
      "output_masks": [
        {"kind": "regex", "path": "/result/content/0/text",
         "pattern": "db:\\s+\\S+",   "replacement": "db:     <masked>"},
        {"kind": "regex", "path": "/result/content/0/text",
         "pattern": "chunks:\\s+\\d+", "replacement": "chunks: <masked>"},
        {"kind": "regex", "path": "/result/content/0/text",
         "pattern": "files:\\s+\\d+",  "replacement": "files:  <masked>"},
        {"kind": "regex", "path": "/result/content/0/text",
         "pattern": "dim:\\s+\\d+",    "replacement": "dim:    <masked>"},
        {"kind": "regex", "path": "/result/contents/0/text",
         "pattern": "db:\\s+\\S+",   "replacement": "db:     <masked>"},
        {"kind": "regex", "path": "/result/contents/0/text",
         "pattern": "chunks:\\s+\\d+", "replacement": "chunks: <masked>"},
        {"kind": "regex", "path": "/result/contents/0/text",
         "pattern": "files:\\s+\\d+",  "replacement": "files:  <masked>"},
        {"kind": "regex", "path": "/result/contents/0/text",
         "pattern": "dim:\\s+\\d+",    "replacement": "dim:    <masked>"}
      ],
      "prerequisites": [
        {"kind": "file", "path": "tools/crag-mcp/crag-mcp"},
        {"kind": "env",  "name": "CRAG_TEST_DB"}
      ]
    }
  ]
}
